    <stitle>SINGLE REDUCTION, TANDEM AXLE: INTERNATIONAL - DISASSEMBLE - PINION</stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="disassemble" graphiccount="2">
        <title>PINION</title>
        <svcsubproc>
            <title>Refer to
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1400918">Figure 18</hotlnk>
            </title>
            <figure id="f1400918" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1400918" filename="../figg14/g1400918.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 18. Forward Rear Axle and Rear Rear Axle Components</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1>1. CARRIER CASE</callout1>
                    <callout1>2. PINION PILOT BEARING</callout1>
                    <callout1>3. DRIVE PINION</callout1>
                    <callout1>4. BEARING CONE</callout1>
                    <callout1>5. BEARING CUP</callout1>
                    <callout1>6. POSITION SHIMS (SELECTIVE)</callout1>
                    <callout1>7. PINION BEARING CAGE</callout1>
                    <callout1>8. PRELOAD SPACER (SELECTIVE)</callout1>
                    <callout1>9. BEARING CUP</callout1>
                    <callout1>10. BEARING CONE</callout1>
                    <callout1>11. DRIVEN GEAR</callout1>
                    <callout1>12. PINION NUT SPACER</callout1>
                    <callout1>13. ROLL PIN</callout1>
                    <callout1>14. CASTELLATED PINION NUT</callout1>
                    <callout1>15. BOLT</callout1>
                    <callout1>16. BOLT</callout1>
                    <callout1>17. PINION NUT</callout1>
                    <callout1>18. END YOKE</callout1>
                    <callout1>19. PINION SEAL</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove pinion cage mounting bolts.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove pinion and cage assembly from carrier housing (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f1400919">Figure 19</hotlnk>). If difficulty is encountered in removing pinion
                    assembly from carrier, place brass drift on inner end of pinion gear and tap lightly.
                </para>
                <figure id="f1400919" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic id="g1400919" filename="../figg14/g1400919.webp" type="webp"/>
                    <caption>Figure 19. Remove Pinion and Cage Assembly From Carrier Housing</caption>
                </figure>
                <specpara>
                    <note>
                        <para>Retain shims for possible use during reassembly.</para>
                    </note>
                </specpara>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Mount pinion assembly in a soft jawed vise or fixture, holding yoke or gear stationary.
                    Remove roll pin, nut, and spacer.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove the end yoke or drive gear, using a suitable press.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove pinion gear from cage assembly.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Located between pinion bearings is a selective spacer, used for pinion bearing preload.
                    Retain this spacer for possible use in reassembly.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove old pinion seal and discard. Always replace it with a new seal at time of
                    reassembly.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Lift out outer pinion bearing cone.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove inner pinion bearing cup, using a suitable adapter and press or puller.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove roller bearing from end of pinion.</para>
                <specpara>
                    <warning>
                        <para>Bearing must be shielded during removal to eliminate possible personal injury if bearing
                            races shatter.
                        </para>
                    </warning>
                </specpara>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove inner bearing cone from pinion gear.</para>
            </step1>
        </svcsubproc>
    </svcproc>
